articles.description: Sean Lloyd Jr. got to the basket for a layup with 14.6 seconds left in regulation to force overtime, then hit a clutch 3-pointer in the extra session to help Southern Illinois pull out a 76-72 win over Indiana State in a key Missouri Valley Conference...
articles.headline: Southern Illinois escapes in OT, beats Indiana State, 76-72

articles.description: Kason Harrell scored 24 points on six 3-pointers and Fort Wayne beat North Dakota State 84-72 on Saturday afternoon.
articles.headline: Fort Wayne holds on for 84-72 win over North Dakota St.

articles.description: Trae Young says it's tougher now for him to score than it was at the beginning of the season because he's being guarded harder now.
articles.headline: Young: 'I'm being guarded like no one else in the country'

images.caption: Trae Young says it's tougher now for him to score than it was at the beginning of the season because he's being guarded harder now.

articles.description: Duke freshman Marvin Bagley III will miss his third straight game Sunday against No. 11 Clemson as he continues to recover from a 'mild' right knee sprain suffered in the first half against North Carolina last week.
articles.headline: Marvin Bagley III to miss third straight game Sunday with right knee sprain

articles.description: J.P. Macura gets the Musketeers off to a hot start, scoring the team's first six points with a pair of 3-pointers.
articles.headline: Xavier's Macura hot from deep early

articles.description: Michigan State holds Northwestern to 11 points in the second half and Cassius Winston finishes with 17 points and 9 rebounds as the Spartans win 65-60.
articles.headline: Spartans overcome 22-point halftime deficit to defeat Wildcats
